{
  "name": "02 — Zoom Giveaway Attendance + Demo Simulator",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 02 — Verified Zoom attendance and demo controls\n\n**Production:** verifies Zoom's HMAC signature, handles endpoint validation, acknowledges valid events quickly, then writes the join/leave state atomically to Postgres.\n\n**Demo:** four manual triggers let you show entrants joining, staff joining, five entrants leaving, and attendance resetting—without access to the creator's Zoom account.",
        "height": 400,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "34bf5021-091b-505f-a1d2-3d01f7bcaf5c",
      "name": "WF2 README",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1220,
        -780
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## One unavoidable non-credential value\n\nOn n8n Cloud Starter, a Code node cannot read a normal credential's secret value. Therefore: edit the `Zoom Webhook Secret — Paste Once` field, run that setup branch once, then replace the field with `SAVED_IN_DATABASE` if desired.\n\nThe real secret is thereafter read from Postgres. This avoids leaving it inside every execution branch.",
        "height": 400,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "21446896-8e4c-5413-ba5e-25fe92b1c39e",
      "name": "WF2 Secret Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -340,
        -780
      ]
    },
